":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIt is not lawful to boycott for more than three days. If the two meet and one greets the other with peace and receives a response, they will share the reward. If the other refuses to\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":860,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/06\/11\/break-peace-treaty-jannah\/","url_meta":{"origin":1982,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Treachery: Betrayal of treaties forbids entry to Paradise","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 11, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever kills a person protected by a treaty will never smell the fragrance of Paradise. Verily, its fragrance can be found from a distance of forty years of travel.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6914 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34651,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/12\/06\/all-paradise-but-stray-camels\/","url_meta":{"origin":1982,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Hereafter: All enter Paradise but those who stray like camels","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 6, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cBy the One in whose hand is my soul, you